# Tailwind CSS v3 Guidelines

## Class Organization

Order Tailwind classes consistently using this pattern:
1. Layout (display, position, z-index)
2. Box model (width, height, margin, padding)
3. Typography (font, text, leading)
4. Visual (background, border, shadow)
5. Interactive (hover, focus, active states)
6. Responsive (sm:, md:, lg:)
7. Dark mode (dark:)

```tsx
// Good: Classes are organized logically
<div className="flex items-center justify-between w-full h-10 px-4 text-sm font-medium bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:bg-gray-50 focus:ring-2 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700" />

// Bad: Random order makes it hard to scan
<div className="hover:bg-gray-50 px-4 flex rounded-lg dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm shadow-sm border-gray-200 items-center" />
```

## Use the `cn()` Utility

Always use the `cn()` utility from `~/lib/utils` for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '~/lib/utils'

// Good: Proper conditional classes with cn()
<button className={cn(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium',
  variant === 'primary' && 'bg-blue-600 text-white',
  variant === 'secondary' && 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900',
  disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'
)} />

// Bad: String concatenation or ternary chains
<button className={`px-4 py-2 ${variant === 'primary' ? 'bg-blue-600' : 'bg-gray-200'}`} />
```

## Dark Mode Implementation

This project uses `darkMode: 'class'`. Always implement both light and dark variants:

```tsx
// Good: Complete light/dark implementation
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 border-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700" />

// Bad: Missing dark mode variants
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 border-gray-200" />
```

### Dark Mode Color Mapping

Use these standard mappings for consistency:
- `bg-white` → `dark:bg-gray-800` or `dark:bg-slate-900`
- `bg-gray-50` → `dark:bg-gray-900`
- `bg-gray-100` → `dark:bg-gray-800`
- `text-gray-900` → `dark:text-gray-100`
- `text-gray-700` → `dark:text-gray-300`
- `text-gray-500` → `dark:text-gray-400`
- `border-gray-200` → `dark:border-gray-700`
- `border-gray-300` → `dark:border-gray-600`

