## Component Patterns

### Variant Pattern with Objects

Use object syntax in `cn()` for cleaner variant handling:

```tsx
<button className={cn(
  'base-styles',
  {
    'bg-blue-600 text-white': variant === 'primary',
    'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900': variant === 'secondary',
    'bg-red-600 text-white': variant === 'danger',
  }
)} />
```

### Size Variants

Standardize size variants across components:

```tsx
const sizeClasses = {
  xs: 'h-6 px-2 text-xs',
  sm: 'h-8 px-3 text-sm',
  md: 'h-10 px-4 text-base',
  lg: 'h-12 px-6 text-lg',
}
```

## Animation Classes

Use the custom animations defined in `tailwind.config.js`:

```tsx
// Available custom animations
<div className="animate-shimmer" />    // Loading shimmer effect
<div className="animate-float" />      // Floating effect
<div className="animate-spin-slow" />  // Slow spin (3s)
<div className="animate-pulse-slow" /> // Slow pulse (3s)
```

For CSS-defined animations in `main.css`:
```tsx
<div className="animate-fade-in-up" />
<div className="animate-fade-in-down" />
<div className="animate-scale-in" />
<div className="animate-gradient" />
```

## Focus States

Always implement proper focus states for accessibility:

```tsx
// Good: Complete focus state implementation
<button className="focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-blue-500 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 dark:focus-visible:ring-offset-gray-800" />

// Bad: Removing focus without replacement
<button className="focus:outline-none" />
```

## Hover States

Use appropriate hover feedback:

```tsx
// Interactive elements need hover states
<button className="hover:bg-blue-700 active:bg-blue-800 transition-colors" />

// Subtle hover for list items
<div className="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-800/50" />
```

## Glass Morphism

Use the `.glass` utility class for glass effects:

```tsx
<div className="glass rounded-lg p-4">
  {/* Automatically handles light/dark mode */}
</div>
```

## Spacing Consistency

Use consistent spacing throughout the app:

- **Padding**: Use `p-2`, `p-3`, `p-4`, `p-6` (avoid arbitrary values)
- **Margins**: Use `m-2`, `m-4`, `m-6`, `m-8`
- **Gaps**: Use `gap-2`, `gap-3`, `gap-4`, `gap-6`

```tsx
// Good: Standard spacing
<div className="p-4 space-y-4">
  <div className="flex gap-3">...</div>
</div>

// Bad: Arbitrary or inconsistent spacing
<div className="p-[13px] space-y-[7px]">...</div>
```

## Responsive Design

Desktop-first approach for this Electron app. Use responsive utilities sparingly:

```tsx
// Only when truly needed for window resizing
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3" />
```

## Scrollbar Styling

Custom scrollbar styles are defined in `main.css`. For scrollable containers:

```tsx
<div className="overflow-y-auto max-h-64">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

## Shadow Utilities

Use custom glow shadows for emphasis:

```tsx
<div className="shadow-glow-blue" />   // Blue glow
<div className="shadow-glow-green" />  // Green glow  
<div className="shadow-glow-purple" /> // Purple glow
```

## Avoid These Anti-patterns

1. **Don't use `@apply` excessively** - Prefer utility classes in JSX
2. **Don't create arbitrary values** - Use the design system
3. **Don't duplicate Tailwind in CSS** - Use config extensions
4. **Don't forget dark mode** - Always test both themes
5. **Don't hardcode colors** - Use the configured palette
